OL,3,CBlue whales are losing their voices,
OL,4,Cbut what is causing the silence?
OL,6,FBlue whales produce one of the loudest
OL,7,Fsongs on Earth, registering up to 188
OL,8,Fdecibels, and their deep melodic tones
OL,9,Fcan be heard from up to 600 miles away.
OL,11,FHowever, scientists who analysed whale
OL,12,Fsongs over six years found that the
OL,13,Flargest mammals on Earth were calling
OL,14,Fless and less, and it's believed
OL,15,Fclimate change is to blame.
