OL,3,CBlue whales are losing their voices,
OL,4,Cbut what is causing the silence?
OL,6,FIn some areas it touched, it raised
OL,7,Fthe average sea temperature by up to
OL,8,F2.5C. By 2016, the area it covered
OL,9,Fspanned over 2,000 miles.
OL,11,FThe temperature change led to toxic
OL,12,Falgae blooms, which killed off krill
OL,13,Fin large swathes.
OL,15,F"We don't hear them singing," John
OL,16,FRyan, a biological oceanographer at
OL,17,Fthe Monterey Bay Aquarium Research
OL,18,FInstitute, told National Geographic.
